review_blob: Pours black with a thick head. Aroma has a bit of chocolate and fruit to it. However, it tastes like cardboard and burnt coffee. Pretty shitty.
Pours amber with a creamy head. Excellent hop aroma. Creamy and bitter with a hint of toffee. This is the perfect representation of cascade hops.
Pours yellow with a very thin head. Very citrus aroma. Crisp and bitter with a slight flavor of leeche. Nice stuff.
Pours golden yellow with a thick white head. Very grassy hop aroma. Taste is a little off putting. the hops taste like wet grass. All in all this is pretty sad.
beer_name: Big Rock Ambrosia Wet Hop Ale

review_blob: pours yellow with almost no head. I can smell the big rock yeast and some rye malt. light and smooth. malty with the slightest note of ginger. The ginger flavour is so light that I dont think I would even notice it if I wasnt looking for it. All in all another shitty Big Rock brew.
pours cloudy amd amber with a thin white head. Bold hop aroma, very pacific North west.Very creamy, citrus, grassy bitter. It is a buffet of hop character. An excellent brew.

Pours black with a thick brown head. Very strong aroma of chocolate and roasted malts. Great flavour. chocolate toasted barley and coffee, all slowly melding together into a very smokey cpicy finish. Fastastic.
Pours golden with a thin head. Aroma is dull. Some spice and banana but not much going on. Creamy mouth feel. Terrible bubblegum after taste. This is just terrible.

Pours golden amber with a very thin head. Aroma is very malt forward with a slight floral hop aroma. Flavor is dull. Grassy and very bitter. Not, great but not horrible. I wish it popped a bit more. More citrus would be nice.
Pours black very thin head. Strong aroma of coffee chocolate. Nice flavor. Bold and rich with a nice hop spice. Nice stout. I like it.
Pours black with a brown head. Great aroma. Roasted malt and chocolate. Tastes great very creamy. An excellent stout.
Pours ambe not red. Nice aroma, yeast hops a little banana . Mic flavor. Very Belgian. Nice brew.
Pours copper with a creamy head. Nicehop aroma mildly citrus. Tastes fine. I get a lot of malt and caramel. Not much of a pale ale.
Pours black thin head. Roasted malt and vanilla in the aroma.  Flavor is very nice chocolate and caramel nice brew a little dark for dunkle. But, very tasty none the less.
beer_name: Half Pints Noche De Los Alebrijes

review_blob: Stray colored with a thin head. Mild malty aroma very smooth and clean with a slightly dry bitter aftertaste. Not offensive at all. Pretty good as Asian lager goes.
Pours hazy amber. Thin white head. (on tap) nice hop aroma very bold and floral. Bitter and easy drinking an excellent pale ale.

pours amber with a very thick head. aroma. nice aroma/ i get citrus and grapefruit. lots of chinook. Nice flavour grassy malty, citrus. bitter. not a bad Ipa. but, its nothing to write home about. bitter and enjoyable, yet unimpressive.
Pours hazy amber with a thick white head. nice aroma. very grassy, the chinook. tastes very nice. bitter and grassy, citrus and amazing. It could be a little fresher. but all in all a very nice brew.
Pours golden with a thin white head. skunky citrus aroma. not bad. tastes fine a bit funky and weird. Not a bad saison but not great. Not sure that its not that great.
pours cloudy yellow with a thin white head. Aroma is very sour. Curls my nose hair. Flavour is very nice. Very sour very bold and very dry an exceptional lambic

Pours pinkish with a thin head. aroma is, very malty with a slight hop zing to it. Thick rich and flavourfull, grat malt profile. I can detect the barrel and it finishes with a nice hop bitterness. Nice brew.

Pours reddish with a white head. Very floral hoot aroma. I get lots of simcoe. Very complex. The hop profile is vast and evolving. With a bitter citrus finish. Once again mikkelller has hoped this one right up. Very nice.
Pours black thin brown head. Smells amazing . I get the barrel and the stout. Flavor is amazing I get alll the geek Plus the barrel. Mikkeller busted it out on this barrel edition. Great.
beer_name: Mikkeller Beer Geek Brunch Weasel (Cognac Edition)

review_blob: Pours black with a thin head. Aroma is very nice. I get a lot of berrel out of this one. Smells amazing. Tastes amazing. The barrel, the calvados, the coffee, the chocolate. This is fucking amazing an amazing an amazing beer.
beer_name: Mikkeller Beer Geek Brunch Weasel (Calvados Edition)

review_blob: Pours amber with thin white head. Very hoppy aroma . Tastes amazing, bitter and citrus, grapefruit grass, hops abound in this brew. Fresh complex and delicious. A fantastic brew plus I love the moth label .Very tangy in the finish. Great brew.

PoUrs yellow with a thin head. Mild skunky hop aroma. Flavor is nice a little thin with mild hops. Not bad at all. Tastes like most Asian lagers, but it is put together very well. Thank you Patrick & Carly & the all the other people along the way who handled this beer to get it to me. Thanks again.

Pours brown with a thick white head.  Very malty aroma with some grassy notes. Rich and malty, I get a hint of cocoa and very delicate hops. A fine beer no doubt. Yet, not so good Im going to rush out and tell all my friends.
pours yellow with a huge white head. Aroma is very spice, clove and corriander. Very nice flavour bold and spicy with lots of banana and clove. A very nice wit beer.

Pours copper with a very thick creamy head. Big hop aroma very floral and grassy. Thick and rich. Very strong hop flavour, bitter grassy and herbal. This is an amazing IPA. I couldnt ask for more. It really is a hop bomb!
Piss yellow with a thin white head. Almost no aroma, I get a little corn. Tastes fine. pretty neutral. Goes down smooth. But it is pretty dull. This is about all I expect out of a miller product.

Pours hazy yellow with a thick white head. Great aroma very fruity, I get some nectarine and very citrus hops. Nice full mouth feel. The flavour is very light and refreshing. slight hop bitterness in the finish and a lot of malt character through out. This is a very nice summer beer. And very refreshing for a bock.
Pours yellow very thin head. Aroma is mild with some hop character. Tastes nice. Mildly bitter a very nice brew just bitter enough. Pretty good.

Pours copper with a nice head . Very citrus aroma smells amazing. Tastes great! Very bitter lots of hops. This is a fantastic session beer. I could drink it every day. Perhaps the best session beer I have ever had. The balance is perfect.

Pours red with a thick white head. Rich malty aroma, like burnt caramel. A bit thin. Nice chocolate flavour late in the palate. Malty and drinkable but severely lacking in body. Im not looking for it to be as thick as stout, But, this stuff is as thin as a pilsener. Tastes nice but a little dull.
Looks like it is mostly Vienna malt. Smells like it as well. But thats not a bad thing. Rich malty flavor. An excellent alt. Sweet and malty. Lots of Vienna. Very nice.
Pours black with a tall beige head. Strong hop aroma with some chocolate to it. Very strong malty toasted flavor. Coffee and chocolate. Although I do loose the hops in the palate.
Pours hazy amber with a thin head. Slightly sour aroma. Malty with some sour yeast. Funky. Very tasty I get some slightly sugary with a salty bite. It reminds me of wine gums in Europe.

Pours copper with a thin white head. Malty caramel aroma. Lots of crystal in this one.  Very malty flavor with a hint of grass and banana. Not bad. Pretty dull. But, I think that is what kristal wizen is all about.

Pours hazy yellow with a thick white head. Smells very nice very strong hops . The Amarillo really comes through in the aroma, as well as the cascade. Tastes nice very citrus and bitter. Lots of grapefruit. Very fresh and crisp. Great brew.

Pours slightly orange with a thick white head and some suspended sediment. Aroma is a little Funky with lots of orange and banana. Tastes nice. Some vanilla and candy. Slightly spicy and citrus. Not bad at all. Pretty middle of the road Belgian blonde.
Pours black thin head. Nice hop aroma grassy and floraland graper. Flavour is nice bold hops. Very bitter. With a bit of a tang to it . Very nice black ipa.
beer_name: Firestone Walker Wookey Jack Black Rye IPA

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Pours hazy amber with a thick white head. Strong hop aroma. Floral and grassy. Excellent flavour. Bitter, with a mild malty character. This is a very nice ipa. But, I wish it was. Little more bitter. Nice brew.
Pours black thin head. Aroma is very strong with plums and raisin. Ful rich malt flavour with a very complex fruit flavour. Very drinkable.,with a perfect favour balance. Great brew.
Pours pale amber with a white head. Smells very oaky. Flavour is amazing bold complex. I get the wine the oak the tannins. Deliciouse. I get marmalade and hops. Very creative and tasty.
Pale amber. White head. Aroma is grassy with lots of yeast. Malty and sweet. Slightly floral aftertaste . A poor ipa.
Pours amber with a cream coloured head. Very nice aroma. Very hopy. Tastes great very citrus. A delicious amber ale.
Pours black white head. Strong aroma of yeast. Flavour is nice bitter hopy malty. Its got it it all. Solid black ipa. I like it.
Pours black with a white head. Smells very hopy. Pacific north west hops. Very nice. Nice flavour. Hops transition into chocolate and roasted malts. And finishes with bitter hops. Very nice.

pours black with a great beige head. Aroma is very fishy. not very nice. Flaour is fantastic. bold roasted malts and chcocolate. very drinkable. medium body. very nice full palate. a very tasty beer.. but the fishy, soy sauce aroma is a real let down.

pours black with a very nice head on it.The aroma is nice hints of chocolate mingling with the hops. Rich full flavour. tones of chocolate and deep roasted malts. A bitter hop bite finishes this one off, making it both bold and complex. The beer is so rich and flavourfull. This is an amazing stout. It has every think I want. strong rich stout flavours and a hell of a bitter hop finish. Great.
